  "contentHtml": "<img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/6e143325-c7c7-37f3-3355-975fc53161bb.png\" width=\"628\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n<p><span>Hey Brew Shop Fam!<br>Here's an update of what's happening this week - from new&nbsp;beer drops, wine reviews, our current tap list, to upcoming tastings, and more.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<a href=\"https://us.list-manage.com/pub864vdHQq?e=01c6cdb4b7&amp;c2id=78b36ba273cb71acbb53a8fce08ea4f0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SHOP THIS WEEK’S NEWSLETTER HERE</a>\n<a href=\"https://us.list-manage.com/AsY3kBGPaTL?e=01c6cdb4b7&amp;c2id=78b36ba273cb71acbb53a8fce08ea4f0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">SHOP OUR ENTIRE STOCK OF BEER, WINE &amp; HOMEBREW HERE</a>\n<img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/8f999745-26c5-bd7d-8dc7-ed37eaaa3e7c.png\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n<p><span><span><span><span>Join us this</span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span> Friday from 5-7 PM</span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span> as we welcome Jackson from&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><strong><span><span><span><span>Nepenthe&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>for our free tasting! Scroll down to see our full tasting line-up for July.</span></span></span></span></p>\n<img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/c402085b-62e5-900c-5040-4884bd350962.png\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n<p>👊 <strong>The Alchemist </strong>returns with<strong> Heady Topper </strong>and<strong> Focal Banger</strong>! Releasing in-store and online when the truck arrives. Limits will apply.</p>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/9b7964ee-2f58-647e-89a2-04da955b72ca.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>👋 A very warm Welcome Back <strong>Half Acre</strong><br>• <strong>Daisy Cutter </strong>West Coast Pale Ale with Simcoe, Centennial, CTZ &amp; Chinook<br>• <strong>Pony </strong>German Pilsner<br>• <strong>Half Acre Light </strong>American Light Lager<br>• <strong>Bodem </strong>West Coast IPA with Mosaic, Cashmere &amp; Idaho 7<br>• <strong>WayBird</strong> Hazy IPA with El Dorado &amp; HBC 586<br>• <strong>Slow Melt</strong> West Coast IPA with Citra &amp; Mosaic<br>• <strong>Vallejo </strong>West Coast IPA with Simcoe &amp; Nelson Sauvin</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/523453c4-cd00-3613-2dbd-cdc0ea1c2a5d.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🤝 Always feeling good with <strong>Bissell Brothers</strong><br>• <strong>Swish </strong>Hazy DIPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; Simcoe<br>• <strong>Swish Silver</strong> Session IPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; Simcoe<br>• <strong>The Substance </strong>IPA with Falconer’s Flight, Centennial, Apollo, Chinook, Summit &amp; Eureka<br>• <strong>Reciprocal</strong> IPA with Australian Vic Secret, Ella &amp; Summer<br>• <strong>Here’s To Feeling Good All the Time</strong> DIPA with Galaxy, Mosaic &amp; Simcoe<br>• <strong>Hearts of Pine</strong> Session Pale Ale with malts only from Maine</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/e1ab9e6e-e250-4a42-db68-cb59e15d914d.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🌳 Stay safe out there with <strong>Fonta Flora</strong><br>• <strong>Doom Tree </strong>Kolsch with lemon zest &amp; elderflower<br>• <strong>Hop Beard </strong>West Coast IPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; Simcoe<br>• <strong>Whoa, Bear </strong>West Coast IPA with Krush Cryo, Chinook &amp; Citra Cryo - collab with <strong>Trophy Brewing</strong><br>• <strong>Life’s Changed </strong>Hazy DIPA with Nectaron, El Dorado Cryo &amp; Krush Hyperboost</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/04941aa2-6129-659b-5321-c913c4127d23.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>✨We won’t forget to remember <strong>Bluejacket</strong><br>• <strong>Lost Weekend</strong> Citra IPA<br>• <strong>Self Portrait</strong> German Pilsner<br>• <strong>Macaulay Macaulay Culkin Culkin</strong> IPA with NZ Cascade, Citra &amp; Mosaic - collab with <strong>The Veil</strong></p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/3051c1da-e322-bde8-bc48-7a6a0b5458a3.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🏠 Farmhouse fun with<br>• <strong>de Garde The Frais a l’Orange </strong>Spontaneous Wild Ale with Orange Zest aged in Oak Barrels<br>• <strong>Oxbow Field Beer</strong> Farmhouse with Herbs &amp; Honey<br>• <strong>Oxbow Loretta</strong> Grisette</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/64ffccf1-4dea-d39a-59f3-94fd583208e8.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🐈‍⬛ Fan favorites from <strong>Jester King </strong>return<br>•<strong> Nani</strong> Rice Lager<br>• <strong>The Satyr</strong> German pilsner<br>• <strong>The Gary's</strong> West Coast IPA with Columbus Cryo, Citra Hyperboost, Simcoe, Mosaic &amp; Citra Cryo<br>• <strong>Dadcore</strong> West Coast Pilsner with Cascade, Simcoe, Mosaic &amp; Columbus - collab with <strong>Goodline Beer</strong></p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/1af52114-2483-4d93-5f23-5491d2d4bfd0.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🧃 All the juice with <strong>Weldwerks</strong><br>• <strong>Juicy Bits </strong>Hazy IPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; El Dorado<br>• <strong>Extra Extra Juicy Bits</strong> Hazy DIPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; El Dorado<br>• <strong>Bamm Bamm Rubble Rubble</strong> Sour &nbsp;with Fruity Pebbles Cereal, Strawberry, Milk Sugar, Vanilla &amp; Marshmallow<br>• <strong>Orange Creamsicle</strong> Sour Ale With Vanilla, Orange Juice &amp; Milk Sugar<br>• <strong>Hens with Benefits</strong> West Coast IPA with Centennial, Chinook, Citra, Lemondrop &amp; Nelson<br>•<strong> Freezer Aisle: Rocky Road </strong>Stout with Almonds, Chocolate, Marshmallow &amp; Milk Sugar<br>• <strong>Guava Lime</strong> <strong>Gose</strong> Sour with Sea Salt, Lime &amp; Guava Puree</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/bccb1c11-eddc-0399-8c67-ad02cb66d23d.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🌈 Don't miss<br>• <strong>Parish 4XDH Envie</strong> Hazy Pale Ale with 4x as much Citra!<br>• <strong>American Solera MOG</strong> DIPA with Galaxy &amp; Citra Hyperboost<br>• <strong>Precarious Rainbow Kittens</strong> IPA with Citra &amp; El Dorado conditioned on Pineapple, Peach, Pink Guava, and Cherries<br>• <strong>Commonwealth Liliko'i Koolie</strong> Sour with Passionfruit, Mango, Guava &amp; Coconut Cream<br>• <strong>Schilling Tenno Dry</strong> Rice Lager</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/5b0ac9bb-98bc-93f3-df98-6b397529e470.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>👊 We love you too, <strong>Sante Adairius</strong><br>• <strong>831 </strong>West Coast IPA with Columbus<br>• <strong>Tomorrow, Today </strong>West Coast IPA with Simcoe, Citra &amp; Mosaic<br>• <strong>Pivots and Dials </strong>American IPA<br>• <strong>Tiny Ladders </strong>Hazy IPA</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/58f8005f-8942-d3d0-7aae-22aa0daaa7a5.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>☠️ VA's own <strong>Adroit Theory</strong> <br>• <strong>Like Darkness to a Dying Flame </strong>West Coast IPA<br>• <strong>Confessions </strong>Russian Imperial Stout</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/5642efbb-8196-2904-bb0b-4b635a598c27.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🍎 <strong>Artifact Cider </strong>is back!<br>• <strong>Slow Down </strong>100% McIntosh Cider<br>• <strong>Feels Like Home </strong>Cider aged on rum soaked oak</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/cd3aa3af-9d59-b84f-8447-b34d7656c853.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🌲 The latest from <strong>Beer Tree</strong><br>• <strong>Star Gazing </strong>Hazy IPA with Citra, Mosaic &amp; Amarillo<br>• <strong>Proper Dose</strong> Hazy IPA with Rakau, Strata, Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo &amp; Galaxy<br>• <strong>Canyons </strong>West Coast IPA with Centennial, Cascade, Chinook, Simcoe, Citra &amp; Nectaron<br>• <strong>Juice Land</strong> Hazy IPA with Mosaic, Strata &amp; Nelson<br>• <strong>Trippy Tree </strong>Berries &amp; Cream Sour with Blackberry, Blueberry, Raspberry, Strawberry, Marshmallow &amp; Vanilla<br>• <strong>Campfire Tales</strong> Imperial Milk Stout with Cocoa Nibs, Graham Cracker &amp; Marshmallow</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/918ba7d2-34e5-3b50-14b5-9bcc7abc8e75.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p><strong>🪦The Veil </strong>keeping things lively<br>• <strong>No More Flowers </strong>Kolsch<br>• <strong>R.I.P. Me</strong> Hazy DIPA with Citra, Citra Lupulin Powder, Nelson &amp; Simcoe</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/2f48319a-15ab-43e2-b848-b2ccb2a3fff6.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p><span><span><span><span><img src=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/e/notoemoji/17.0/1f31f/72.png\" alt=\"🌟\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></span></span></span></span>Fresh in from <strong>Nepenthe</strong> <br>• <strong>Geistbar</strong> Marzen style Oktoberfest<br>• <strong>Queen Jellyfish</strong> Hazy DIPA with Galaxy, Motueka &amp; Simcoe</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/9cbf6b60-2f11-8aae-2a52-cf1dda0018f4.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🌞 Freshies from <strong>Grimm</strong><br>• <strong>Underwater Sunlight </strong>Hazy IPA with Nectaron, Cashmere, Citra &amp; Columbus<br>• <strong>Hyperfocus </strong>Citra Hazy DIPA</p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/575d3627-c7cb-9b21-e480-23e9924a7840.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p><img src=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/e/notoemoji/17.0/1f504/72.png\" alt=\"🔄\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"> Opposites attract with<br>• <strong>Benchtop 1500</strong> Czech Pale Lager<br>• <strong>Oskar Blues Ten Fidy </strong>Imperial Stout</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<div class=\"reader-image-row reader-brew-grid\" data-columns=\"2\"><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/3e5ae88d-9774-6d02-9caa-156583bd6e63.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p>🥨 Feeling festie</p>\n<p>• <strong>Right Proper Senate Maerzen </strong><br>• <strong>Full Distance Festiber</strong></p>\n<p>• <strong>Tucher Festbier</strong><br>• <strong>Best Day Non-Alcoholic Oktoberfest</strong></p></figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/5b5bb4e0-8b33-1dcf-2899-01ffa8707d80.jpeg\" width=\"298\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><figcaption><p><img src=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/e/notoemoji/17.0/1f383/72.png\" alt=\"🎃\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"> Yes, it's happening people</p>\n<p>• <strong>Ommegang All Hallows Treat</strong> Imperial Chocolate Peanut Butter Stout<br>•<strong> Downeast Pumpkin </strong>Cider</p>\n<p>Triple Crossing Clever Girl Hazy IPA</p>\n<p>Port City Kolsch</p></figcaption></figure></div>\n<img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/833f81b9-740d-f1a1-d37d-88b5dd1665e7.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n<p><strong><span>Evolucio Furmint</span><span>:</span></strong><span><span><span><span>We're all smiles after our first sip of Hungarian wine. Surprise, Tokaj, Hungary has the world's oldest wine classification system dating way back in 1730 - a whopping 120 years before Bordeaux got around to it. Made from Furmint grown on volcanic soil, Evolucio is bright and zippy with green apple, peach, lemon and wet stone minerality. Hand harvested, Sustainable.</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><strong>Gateway Vinho Verde</strong>: <span><span><span><span>At just 9.5% ABV with a delicate natural fizz, this is the wine you reach for when you want something ridiculously refreshing (without ending up horizontal). The blend of three native grapes come together with lemon-lime, apple and grapefruit. We certainly wouldn't pass judgement if you wanted to dress this one up with a squirt of lime, a dash of soda water or use it as the base for Sangria!</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><strong>Zlatan Dalmatia Marina \"Bilo Idro\": </strong><span><span><span><span>Zlatan Plenković started out as a humble fisherman on the island of Hvar, then in 1991 — the same year Croatia declared independence from Yugoslavia — he founded the country's second-ever private winery, building his cellar from limestone boulders dug right out of the cliffs above the Adriatic Sea. Marina is a mineral-driven field blend of indigenous Croatian varietals that transports you to the Dalmatian coast and into a seat at Zlatan's marina side restaurant Bilo Idro. Peach and citrus mingle with sea air-inspired salinity. Organic &amp; Hand Harvested</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><strong>Francis Blanchet Pouilly-Fumé Kriotine</strong>: <span><span><span><span>The appellation of Pouilly-Fumé (just a stone's throw away from Sancerre) is characterized by an unmistakable flinty or smoky aroma—hence, the name fumé which means “smoked” in French. It is my personal favorite take on Sauvignon Blanc where the minerality is front and center. Kriotine Pouilly-Fumé is divine with crushed oyster shells and flint paired with crisp pear, lime and a dash of sea salt. Hand Harvested, Native Yeast &amp; Sustainable.</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><strong><span><span><span><span>Mr. Brightside Gamay Noir</span></span></span></span></strong><span><span><span><span>: </span></span><span><span>Two of my loves collide with this bottle: Gamay and an unintentional reference to The Killers. Tim Fulnecky is laser focused on Gamay from a single organically-farmed vineyard in Arroyo Seco in Monterey. Tim has produced 15 different wines exclusively from Gamay Noir proving that California's cool coastal climate can rival Beaujolais for pure, electric Gamay character. Mr. Brightside is a gorgeous ruby red with a juicy palate of strawberry, raspberry, violets and a hint of earthiness. Dangerously easy to drink, especially with a chill. Organic &amp; Native Yeast.</span></span></span></span></p>\n<img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/d711c6f0-4654-67d7-0614-9c337e7784c8.jpeg\" width=\"520\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n<p><span><span><span>Calling all seafood lovers...or honestly anyone that wants to lounge by the water with a bottle of minerally white. I’m convinced Andrew Jones has a sixth sense for making wines that disappear from our shelves, and this one is no exception. As the guy behind Field Recordings, he spends his days working with vineyards across California, which means he has a knack for sniffing out the overlooked sites that end up making the most interesting wines. Turns out that pays off. Allow me to introduce your next summer favorite: </span></span></span><strong><span><span><span>Field Recordings - Shucks.</span></span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span><span><span>It's a blend of Pinot Blanc and Melon de Bourgogne from the old La Puesta vineyard in Chalone, CA, which is a bit inland from Monterey Bay tucked up near Pinnacles National Park. Decades ago the Melon vines were mistakenly planted as Pinot Blanc, and over the years the vineyard has become a bit of a mystery mix of the two. I'm fairly confident I drove past the vineyard when I visited Pinnacles a few years ago, and I can totally see how the climate would make for an interesting player here. Warm days ripen the fruit, cool nighttime Bay breezes</span><span> keep everything crisp, and the rocky limestone soils (which if you know much about Cali geology, is a pretty rare find) seem to encourage that salty, stony personality. Where was this when I finished a 10-mile hike in Pinnacles? Instead of having a victory glass of this beauty I had a struggle cup of ramen noodles…..rude. But truly, I feel like this was made to be sipped overlooking Monterey Bay, not sweating in the back of a camper van.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span><span><span><br>Shucks is bright, refreshing, and ridiculously easy to love. It has that clean, ocean-breeze kind of freshness with crunchy green apple, lemon, and a beautiful salty melon kind of minerality. The wine spends a few months resting on its lees which gives it just enough texture for a slight creaminess without taking away from its refreshing edge, or as I like to call it, crispy but not too crispy. It obviously shines with oysters (hence the name), but it's just as happy alongside fish tacos, grilled shrimp, fried seafood, roast chicken, or a picnic by the water. If your ideal summer day involves sunshine, salty air, and something cold in your glass, this bottle understood the assignment.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><em><span><span><span><span>This week’s writeup is brought to you by Aidan</span></span></span></span></em></p>\n<img src=\"https://mcusercontent.com/be20bbfba341582993786f7f0/images/93cbc131-2a72-e677-7905-77d76bf5a954.png\" width=\"534\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\">\n<p><span><span>July Tasting Events coming your way!</span></span></p>\n<p>Thanks for your business! See you soon, Beth, Julie &amp; Aidan and the entire Brew Crew</p>",
